@Scitator, looks better in terms of refactoring, but lacks of expressiveness. 
I would rather suggest to use dict, like this:
```
class SupervisedRunner(Runner):
    def __init__(
        self,
        model: Model = None,
        device: Device = None,
        input_keys: Dict[str, Any] = {"features": ..., "targets": ...}, 
        output_keys: Any = "logits",
    ):
```
it would be easier to distinguish features and targets, doensn't lack of expressiveness, but still looks better in terms of  refactoring.
